body:
by **xianrenb**:

<pre>What steps will reproduce the problem?
run gofmt on the following code:
package main

import (
        &quot;fmt&quot;
)

func main() {
        fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
        if true {
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
        }
        fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
        fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
        if true {
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
        }
        if true {
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
        }
        fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
        fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
        if true {
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
        }
        fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
}

What is the expected output?
expected output code:
package main

import (
        &quot;fmt&quot;
)

func main() {
        fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)

        if true {
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
        }

        fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
        fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)

        if true {
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
        }

        if true {
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
        }

        fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
        fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)

        if true {
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
                fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
        }

        fmt.Println(&quot;ok&quot;)
}

What do you see instead?
code unchanged.


Which compiler are you using (5g, 6g, 8g, gccgo)?
n/a


Which operating system are you using?
Windows 7 SP 1 (32 bit)


Which version are you using?  (run 'go version')
go1.0.3

Please provide any additional information below.
I think future version of gofmt should do a better job in multi-line formatting. Code
blocks should be identified and blank lines should be inserted between them as
illustrated above. Thanks.</pre>
